But EQ2 is sounding a LOT like "Dark Ages of Norrath" in some of the changes they are making. <p><center><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Tuvan/fullsize/tuvansig.jpg><BR><a target="new" href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27793>Tuvan</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 632<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/02 6:15:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2434.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Be honest</span><hr size=1> There are very few original ideas in MMORPG's.  MMORPG's evolved directly from  MUD's.  EQ is very very very similar to a dikumud in design for instance.<br>
<br>
Based on what we know of EQ2, to suggest that it's stealing specific ideas from another MMORPG would be wildly inaccurate. Most elements of these games have already been done before on muds already.  Are they stealing from muds?  Pen and paper RPG's?  Fantasy literature?  To some degree, of course.  You can dissect just about anything and say the same thing though.<br>
<br>
If anything, EQ is somewhat innovative in terms of its interface, implementing a MUD in a 3D world.  DAOC has certainly borrowed from that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
EQ2 needs to be a very different beast than EQ.  The MMORPG genre still very much in its infancy and in order for new games to be successful, they need to evolve the genre.<br>
<br>
For those who don't like change, I'm sure that EQ will be around for a very long time.  id wouldn't be around right now if they stuck to making expansions for the original Wolfenstein or if Doom/Quake/Etc didn't add new gameplay to the genre.<br>
